{"cursor":"2299","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Alexander Bernstein, Baron Bernstein of Craigweil' (15 March 1936 â€“ 13\nApril 2010) Jessica Elgot [http://www.thejc.com/news/uk-news/30336/labour-peer-lord-bernstein-\ndies \"Labour peer Lord Bernstein dies\"], The Jewish Chronicle (website), 13\nApril 2010 was a British television executive and a Labour member of the\nHouse of Lords.\n\nEducated at Stowe School and St John's College, Cambridge, [http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/finance-\nobituaries/7604321/Lord-Bernstein-of-Craigweil.html Obituary: Lord Bernstein\nof Craigweil], Daily Telegraph (website), 18 April 2010 Bernstein joined\nthe Granada Group, the leisure and television company founded by his uncle\nSidney and his father Cecil Bernstein. He was a director of the company,\nmanaging director of Granada Television in the 1970s, and Chairman of Granada\nGroup 1979-96.\n\nBernstein was a major contributor to the Labour Leader's Office Fund run by Lord\nLevy to finance Tony Blair's private office. He was made a life peer as 'Baron\nBernstein of Craigweil', of Craigweil in the County of West Sussex in\n2000. David Osler\n[http://www.whatnextjournal.co.uk/Pages/Back/Wnext25/Osler.html \"Taking It On\nTrust\"],What Next? no.25, 2003 He was also active in the arts, serving on\nseveral governing bodies and trusts.\n\nHe married Vanessa Anne Mills in 1962; they had a son and a daughter, and\ndivorced in 1993. In 1995, he married Angela Mary Serota, the former wife of Sir\nNicholas Serota.\n","linknr":108,"url":"Alexander_Bernstein,_Baron_Bernstein_of_Craigweil","recorded":1364158660,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Alexander_Bernstein,_Baron_Bernstein_of_Craigweil&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Alexander_Bernstein,_Baron_Bernstein_of_Craigweil&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/license